1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:32,001
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:37,605 --> 00:00:40,215
[This drama is fictional and any similarity
with reality is purely coincidental.]

3
00:00:40,215 --> 00:00:42,538
[Production guidelines were followed
when filming children and animals.]

4
00:00:42,538 --> 00:00:44,872
[Episode 8]

5
00:00:44,872 --> 00:00:46,505
Hello.

6
00:00:46,505 --> 00:00:47,738
- Hello.
- You're here.

7
00:00:47,738 --> 00:00:49,438
Hello.

8
00:00:50,872 --> 00:00:52,605
Welcome.

9
00:00:57,438 --> 00:00:59,605
Taxi!

10
00:01:03,572 --> 00:01:04,938
I'll explain later.

11
00:01:04,938 --> 00:01:05,972
Please sit.

12
00:01:05,972 --> 00:01:07,905
You don't need to explain.

13
00:01:09,305 --> 00:01:12,438
I'm sorry, but I wasn't informed
about this blind date today.

14
00:01:12,438 --> 00:01:14,805
I said I'll explain everything.

15
00:01:14,805 --> 00:01:17,172
Please, have a seat first.

16
00:01:17,172 --> 00:01:21,672
No, I think this happened because
my mother doesn't know who I'm seeing.

17
00:01:21,672 --> 00:01:24,305
I apologize for what happened today.

18
00:01:24,305 --> 00:01:26,972
Let's just pretend this never happened.

19
00:01:29,972 --> 00:01:31,372
Hey!

20
00:01:31,372 --> 00:01:33,072
Hey!

21
00:01:48,605 --> 00:01:50,538
Jang Hui Won?

22
00:02:04,772 --> 00:02:08,038
What? Why are you here, Hui Won?

23
00:02:08,038 --> 00:02:10,738
Well, I...

24
00:02:22,505 --> 00:02:24,738
Don't do this blind date.

25
00:02:31,038 --> 00:02:32,905
I like you.

26
00:03:26,205 --> 00:03:28,305
This is me.

27
00:03:29,405 --> 00:03:32,072
Oh, that was quick.

28
00:03:32,072 --> 00:03:33,072
Indeed.

29
00:03:33,072 --> 00:03:36,272
If you have any questions
about the blind date...

30
00:03:36,272 --> 00:03:40,105
You didn't know it was a blind date,
and your mother arranged it on her own.

31
00:03:40,105 --> 00:03:42,772
I've almost memorized it.

32
00:03:44,705 --> 00:03:47,472
It's late. You should go.

33
00:03:48,472 --> 00:03:53,638
Wow, seeing this place like this,
it looks really beautiful.

34
00:03:53,638 --> 00:03:55,672
What time are you going to work tomorrow?

35
00:03:55,672 --> 00:03:57,705
- Why do you ask?
- I was thinking we could go together.

36
00:03:57,705 --> 00:04:01,772
Huh? We mustn't let it show at work. Okay?

37
00:04:01,772 --> 00:04:03,205
I know that much.

38
00:04:03,205 --> 00:04:05,238
But just in case.

39
00:04:05,905 --> 00:04:10,338
Shall we just take one more
quick walk around here?

40
00:04:10,338 --> 00:04:13,805
So we ended up walking two more laps.

41
00:04:13,805 --> 00:04:15,605
You should go now.

42
00:04:15,605 --> 00:04:17,705
We'll see each other at work anyway.

43
00:04:17,705 --> 00:04:19,438
Got it.

44
00:04:21,938 --> 00:04:23,905
But

45
00:04:23,905 --> 00:04:25,772
is what you said earlier for real?

46
00:04:25,772 --> 00:04:29,938
You know, all that stuff about being clingy
and that we should go our separate ways.

47
00:04:29,938 --> 00:04:31,572
I'm not sure if I really believe this.

48
00:04:31,572 --> 00:04:35,472
I'm also worried you might
change your mind again.

49
00:04:35,472 --> 00:04:37,172
It's a bit...

50
00:04:37,905 --> 00:04:39,605
I mean, it's just...

51
00:04:48,172 --> 00:04:49,872
Ugh, whatever.

52
00:04:51,438 --> 00:04:54,472
Wow, such a clear answer.

53
00:04:55,972 --> 00:04:59,205
Oh dear, oh dear.

54
00:04:59,205 --> 00:05:01,505
What an embarrassment!

55
00:05:01,505 --> 00:05:03,538
- Ms. Kim.
- Yes.

56
00:05:03,538 --> 00:05:07,005
Did you know Du Jun is seeing someone?

57
00:05:07,005 --> 00:05:09,872
Is the young master dating someone?

58
00:05:09,872 --> 00:05:14,372
I need to know if it's true
or if he's just making excuses.

59
00:05:14,372 --> 00:05:18,405
And besides, that Mi Ran.
I don't think she's the one I'm looking for.

60
00:05:18,405 --> 00:05:22,938
Her tone and voice are different, I'm sure.

61
00:05:22,938 --> 00:05:26,672
I should have seen her face
back then somehow.

62
00:05:26,672 --> 00:05:28,472
Anyway,

63
00:05:28,472 --> 00:05:31,272
please see

64
00:05:31,272 --> 00:05:33,172
if you can find her.

65
00:05:33,172 --> 00:05:34,672
Yes, understood.

66
00:05:34,672 --> 00:05:41,238
Oh dear.

67
00:05:57,205 --> 00:06:00,072
Ugh, jeez.

68
00:06:00,072 --> 00:06:02,972
Ah, I'm being so foolish.

69
00:06:15,572 --> 00:06:17,705
Yes, hello?

70
00:06:17,705 --> 00:06:18,738
Did you sleep well?

71
00:06:18,738 --> 00:06:19,972
Yes.

72
00:06:19,972 --> 00:06:22,238
Did you sleep well, President?

73
00:06:22,238 --> 00:06:23,505
Yeah, I also slept well.

74
00:06:23,505 --> 00:06:24,772
President, didn't you say

75
00:06:24,772 --> 00:06:28,972
you usually can't sleep well
because of insomnia or something?

76
00:06:28,972 --> 00:06:31,238
That's right. I usually can't sleep well.

77
00:06:31,238 --> 00:06:33,705
But thanks to someone, I slept like a baby.

78
00:06:35,805 --> 00:06:37,938
Not because of the blind date, right?

79
00:06:37,938 --> 00:06:40,372
Ah... well, I was pretty
wiped out from it after all.

80
00:06:40,372 --> 00:06:42,272
What?

81
00:06:43,305 --> 00:06:46,205
Ah, I...

82
00:06:46,205 --> 00:06:47,538
already miss you.

83
00:06:47,538 --> 00:06:50,538
I kind of miss you too.

84
00:06:50,538 --> 00:06:52,305
Today's Kang Du Jun.

85
00:06:52,305 --> 00:06:54,005
What did you just say?

86
00:06:54,005 --> 00:06:55,505
Did you call me by my name?

87
00:06:55,505 --> 00:06:56,705
Say it again.

88
00:06:56,705 --> 00:06:58,672
Huh? Say what?

89
00:06:58,672 --> 00:07:00,538
You just said my name.

90
00:07:00,538 --> 00:07:02,405
Just say it one more time.

91
00:07:02,405 --> 00:07:03,405
No.

92
00:07:03,405 --> 00:07:06,505
Why? It felt friendly and nice. Just once.

93
00:07:06,505 --> 00:07:07,672
I'm hungry.

94
00:07:07,672 --> 00:07:09,705
Aren't you hungry, President?

95
00:07:09,705 --> 00:07:10,705
Why are you changing the subject?

96
00:07:10,705 --> 00:07:12,238
I usually don't eat breakfast.

97
00:07:12,238 --> 00:07:15,705
But if someone asked me
to eat together, I might gladly join.

98
00:07:15,705 --> 00:07:19,672
It's not like I'm saying
we have to eat together right now.

99
00:07:19,672 --> 00:07:23,372
Jang Hui Won, you know,
you're really good at torturing people.

100
00:07:23,372 --> 00:07:25,405
Hope torture.

101
00:07:25,405 --> 00:07:28,072
Well, I guess that's my charm.

102
00:07:28,072 --> 00:07:29,805
Jeez.

103
00:07:30,905 --> 00:07:34,181
I'm in a rush and need to get ready.

104
00:07:34,181 --> 00:07:35,717
We'll

105
00:07:35,717 --> 00:07:39,538
have a meal together soon.

106
00:07:39,538 --> 00:07:41,238
I'll hang up now.

107
00:07:42,938 --> 00:07:44,672
[Jang Hui Won]

108
00:07:46,672 --> 00:07:48,905
We.

109
00:07:48,905 --> 00:07:51,038
Right, 'we.'

110
00:07:54,638 --> 00:07:55,638
Good morning.

111
00:07:55,638 --> 00:07:58,438
- Oh, good morning.
- Good morning.

112
00:07:58,438 --> 00:08:00,005
Manager Jang, anything good happening lately?

113
00:08:00,005 --> 00:08:02,172
Right, you're looking
especially bright today.

114
00:08:02,172 --> 00:08:04,438
Oh, this... it's just...

115
00:08:04,438 --> 00:08:05,838
- Just what?
- What is it?

116
00:08:05,838 --> 00:08:07,705
Oh, well...

117
00:08:07,705 --> 00:08:09,438
It's a dress to cover my belly.

118
00:08:09,438 --> 00:08:11,872
I've gained some weight recently, you see.

119
00:08:11,872 --> 00:08:14,172
Just pretend you don't notice.

120
00:08:14,172 --> 00:08:15,938
Sorry.

121
00:08:18,605 --> 00:08:20,872
- Sorry.
- Sorry.

122
00:08:49,305 --> 00:08:50,572
You look pretty today.

123
00:08:50,572 --> 00:08:52,372
[Jang Hui Won]
Makes me want to ask you out.

124
00:08:54,505 --> 00:08:56,105
What?

125
00:08:56,105 --> 00:09:00,305
[President Kang Du Jun]
Why don't you try kidnapping me then?

126
00:09:18,205 --> 00:09:22,038
Secretary Go, please set your phone
to vibrate in public places.

127
00:09:22,038 --> 00:09:24,305
Ah, just a moment.

128
00:09:28,272 --> 00:09:29,438
I'm sorry.

129
00:09:29,438 --> 00:09:31,672
If you're going to apologize,
do it properly, okay?

130
00:09:37,445 --> 00:09:40,197
Ugh.

131
00:09:41,738 --> 00:09:42,772
- Now.
- What's now?

132
00:09:42,772 --> 00:09:43,838
- What?
- What is it?

133
00:09:43,838 --> 00:09:46,772
Now's the perfect time
to have a snack before lunch.

134
00:09:46,772 --> 00:09:48,172
- So it's now.
- Manager.

135
00:09:48,172 --> 00:09:49,672
Do you still feel bitter about
not getting any snacks?

136
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:53,672
You ate all the madeleines Se Hyeon
brought from France last time,

137
00:09:53,672 --> 00:09:54,705
and I didn't get any.

138
00:09:54,705 --> 00:09:56,272
- Me neither.
- What a shame.

139
00:09:56,272 --> 00:09:58,605
- But the two of us ate them.
- We did?

140
00:09:58,605 --> 00:10:01,038
- It's because of his three kids.
- You didn't get any back then?

141
00:10:01,038 --> 00:10:02,038
What?

142
00:10:02,038 --> 00:10:05,838
I'll bring something more delicious
for everyone next time, except Manager Nah.

143
00:10:05,838 --> 00:10:08,613
Fine, I'll go on a trip too
and buy for everyone except Se Hyeon.

144
00:10:08,613 --> 00:10:10,538
Oh, my.

145
00:10:10,538 --> 00:10:12,038
Team Leader!

146
00:10:12,038 --> 00:10:13,738
To boost work efficiency,
how about a snack break?

147
00:10:13,738 --> 00:10:18,272
In my opinion, work efficiency would
skyrocket if you would just stop talking.

148
00:10:18,272 --> 00:10:20,972
Everyone, dismissed!

149
00:10:20,972 --> 00:10:22,905
The snack delivery is here!

150
00:10:23,557 --> 00:10:25,672
Oh my goodness.

151
00:10:25,672 --> 00:10:28,572
It seemed like the perfect snack time.

152
00:10:28,572 --> 00:10:29,638
As expected of our president!

153
00:10:29,638 --> 00:10:31,238
President, I respect and love you.

154
00:10:31,238 --> 00:10:33,838
How did you even think
to get snacks for us too?

155
00:10:33,838 --> 00:10:35,538
Because it's pretty.

156
00:10:38,872 --> 00:10:40,405
The desserts looked so pretty,

157
00:10:40,405 --> 00:10:42,705
so I thought it'd be nice
if we all shared them.

158
00:10:42,705 --> 00:10:45,605
They say beautiful things taste good too,
and this is completely delicious.

159
00:10:45,605 --> 00:10:48,305
I know, it's completely sweet and refreshing.

160
00:10:48,305 --> 00:10:51,938
I wonder who they're for?

161
00:10:51,938 --> 00:10:54,338
Here, have some drinks too.

162
00:10:58,272 --> 00:11:00,805
We have a meeting, so we'll head out first.

163
00:11:00,805 --> 00:11:02,472
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

164
00:11:02,472 --> 00:11:06,372
I made it super tangy, with lots of ice.

165
00:11:06,372 --> 00:11:08,472
- Secretary Go.
- Oh, jeez.

166
00:11:08,472 --> 00:11:11,438
- Secretary Go.
- Oh, that startled me.

167
00:11:11,438 --> 00:11:12,572
Yes, I'm going.

168
00:11:12,572 --> 00:11:15,105
Ah, then I'll take my leave too.

169
00:11:15,105 --> 00:11:16,838
Yes.

170
00:11:21,061 --> 00:11:22,705
[I Love U]

171
00:11:22,705 --> 00:11:24,438
Team Leader, you said you weren't
going to have any snacks?

172
00:11:24,438 --> 00:11:26,705
Oh, I have to try this one.

173
00:11:26,705 --> 00:11:28,638
It's really tasty.

174
00:11:28,638 --> 00:11:31,972
I don't know why I get
so tired after just eating lunch.

175
00:11:31,972 --> 00:11:34,172
It's a food coma, total food coma.

176
00:11:34,172 --> 00:11:35,472
- Yeah.
- Want to grab coffee?

177
00:11:35,472 --> 00:11:37,305
Sure, where to?

178
00:11:37,305 --> 00:11:39,072
That cafe you mentioned back then.

179
00:11:39,072 --> 00:11:40,805
- Cute!
- Let's try it.

180
00:11:40,805 --> 00:11:43,772
That cafe in front of
the company you mentioned.

181
00:11:43,772 --> 00:11:45,672
Then let's go to the cafe
in front of that company.

182
00:11:45,672 --> 00:11:46,705
Manager.

183
00:11:46,705 --> 00:11:47,738
- Huh?
- Are you hot?

184
00:11:47,738 --> 00:11:50,885
Right, why is your face so red?

185
00:11:50,885 --> 00:11:52,272
Oh.

186
00:11:52,272 --> 00:11:53,872
It suddenly got hot.

187
00:11:53,872 --> 00:11:55,872
Aren't you feeling hot?

188
00:11:56,505 --> 00:11:57,972
Am I the only one feeling this hot?

189
00:11:57,972 --> 00:11:59,038
Assistant Manager, are you hot?

190
00:11:59,038 --> 00:12:00,738
I'm cold.

191
00:12:02,572 --> 00:12:03,605
- What?
- What?

192
00:12:03,605 --> 00:12:04,905
What?

193
00:12:04,905 --> 00:12:05,972
So you do all kinds of things, huh?

194
00:12:05,972 --> 00:12:07,405
Darn it, stop copying me.

195
00:12:07,405 --> 00:12:09,272
What did you say? What did you say?

196
00:12:09,272 --> 00:12:11,005
What did you say?

197
00:12:12,472 --> 00:12:13,972
Oh dear.

198
00:12:13,972 --> 00:12:16,738
You're making such a scene
just to show it off. Totally losing it, huh?

199
00:12:16,738 --> 00:12:17,905
Did it show?

200
00:12:17,905 --> 00:12:18,938
Yeah, totally.

201
00:12:18,938 --> 00:12:22,738
Why are you just openly walking around
like it's Day 1 of dating?

202
00:12:22,738 --> 00:12:25,472
Hui Won said we absolutely
shouldn't let it show.

203
00:12:25,472 --> 00:12:27,738
But if even her yawns are that cute,
what am I supposed to do?

204
00:12:27,738 --> 00:12:30,005
What are you supposed to do?

205
00:12:32,772 --> 00:12:35,438
But she did look tired.

206
00:12:35,438 --> 00:12:36,572
Si Hyeong, aren't you tired?

207
00:12:36,572 --> 00:12:37,938
No, I'm not tired.

208
00:12:37,938 --> 00:12:39,738
All of this is because
I've been keeping myself in shape.

209
00:12:39,738 --> 00:12:41,638
No, you must be tired, Si Hyeong.

210
00:12:41,638 --> 00:12:43,438
Especially after going out
to buy dessert earlier.

211
00:12:43,438 --> 00:12:45,438
I drove, so I'm not tired at all.

212
00:12:45,438 --> 00:12:48,738
No, Si Hyeong, you're clearly
exhausted right now.

213
00:12:48,738 --> 00:12:51,372
Look at your face,
dark circles and dull skin.

214
00:12:51,372 --> 00:12:52,572
- You didn't sleep last night, did you?
- No.

215
00:12:52,572 --> 00:12:53,605
I said I'm not tired.

216
00:12:53,605 --> 00:12:54,638
No.

217
00:12:54,638 --> 00:12:57,405
You're exactly in need of a break right now.

218
00:13:03,805 --> 00:13:07,105
We have an urgent announcement.

219
00:13:07,105 --> 00:13:10,805
For the next two hours,
to help our staff recharge,

220
00:13:10,805 --> 00:13:12,272
the President has initiated nap time...

221
00:13:12,272 --> 00:13:13,405
Nap time?

222
00:13:13,405 --> 00:13:14,672
This is the first time, right?

223
00:13:14,672 --> 00:13:17,738
So, does that mean every employee
is being forced to rest for two hours?

224
00:13:17,738 --> 00:13:20,772
More than forced, isn't it considerate?

225
00:13:20,772 --> 00:13:22,172
Wow, as expected of our president.

226
00:13:22,172 --> 00:13:24,472
The perks are amazing.

227
00:13:26,538 --> 00:13:28,672
No more yawning in front of colleagues.

228
00:13:28,672 --> 00:13:30,338
It's way too dangerously charming.

229
00:13:30,338 --> 00:13:32,838
What? Is he allowed to do this?

230
00:13:32,838 --> 00:13:33,972
Oh, jeez.

231
00:13:33,972 --> 00:13:35,805
What?

232
00:13:35,805 --> 00:13:36,805
Is that your boyfriend?

233
00:13:36,805 --> 00:13:38,805
Pardon?

234
00:13:38,805 --> 00:13:39,838
Why are you so happy?

235
00:13:39,838 --> 00:13:40,872
Manager, do you have a boyfriend?

236
00:13:40,872 --> 00:13:42,105
What, you didn't even tell us?

237
00:13:42,105 --> 00:13:45,172
What boyfriend? He's just a friend.

238
00:13:45,172 --> 00:13:47,438
I mean, when would I have time to date?

239
00:13:47,438 --> 00:13:49,872
True, she's always all about work.

240
00:13:49,872 --> 00:13:51,505
When would she even have time to see a guy?

241
00:13:51,505 --> 00:13:52,872
That's true.

242
00:13:52,872 --> 00:13:55,172
Exactly, I'm working even now.

243
00:13:55,172 --> 00:13:56,372
Se Hyeon.

244
00:13:56,372 --> 00:13:59,472
Can you send me the file
you were supposed to send?

245
00:13:59,472 --> 00:14:01,205
Yes.

246
00:14:08,805 --> 00:14:11,238
Manager, could it be that
she really has a boyfriend?

247
00:14:11,238 --> 00:14:13,272
Right?

248
00:14:13,272 --> 00:14:15,872
Manager Jang does seem different today.

249
00:14:15,872 --> 00:14:17,505
I totally get the vibe of being in love.

250
00:14:17,505 --> 00:14:21,205
No, really. Why is everyone
suddenly so interested in me today?

251
00:14:21,205 --> 00:14:22,572
I really don't have a boyfriend.

252
00:14:22,572 --> 00:14:23,572
So drop this now.

253
00:14:23,572 --> 00:14:26,105
Come on, if you have one, just tell us.

254
00:14:26,105 --> 00:14:27,138
Your skin looks different though?

255
00:14:27,138 --> 00:14:29,505
Don't tell me yesterday...

256
00:14:29,505 --> 00:14:31,305
- It changed?
- Yeah.

257
00:14:34,853 --> 00:14:36,772
Jeez.

258
00:14:36,772 --> 00:14:37,772
Manager.

259
00:14:37,772 --> 00:14:39,205
Here for the contest meeting?

260
00:14:39,205 --> 00:14:40,772
Isn't that scheduled for the afternoon?

261
00:14:40,772 --> 00:14:42,738
No.

262
00:14:42,738 --> 00:14:45,638
Ah, yes, correct.

263
00:14:45,638 --> 00:14:47,472
- But...
- So you came to see Manager Jang?

264
00:14:47,472 --> 00:14:48,805
I'll call Manager Jang for you.

265
00:14:48,805 --> 00:14:50,538
No need.

266
00:14:52,421 --> 00:14:54,053
I just told you...

267
00:14:56,933 --> 00:15:01,138
Oh, I didn't come to see Hui Won.

268
00:15:01,138 --> 00:15:04,438
Ah, the meeting is this afternoon.

269
00:15:04,438 --> 00:15:07,005
That should be in the group chat notice.

270
00:15:07,005 --> 00:15:10,638
I'll double-check and then...

271
00:15:10,638 --> 00:15:12,005
Yeah? Then I'll tell Manager Jang.

272
00:15:12,005 --> 00:15:14,338
- No.
- Fine, go ahead.

273
00:15:14,338 --> 00:15:15,938
- I'll go ahead.
- Yeah.

274
00:15:15,938 --> 00:15:19,005
Manager, I'll confirm it
and come back this afternoon.

275
00:15:19,005 --> 00:15:21,138
Sure, Assistant Manager Cha.

276
00:15:21,138 --> 00:15:23,138
- Take care.
- Yes.

277
00:15:26,172 --> 00:15:28,238
President, on the office floor,

278
00:15:28,238 --> 00:15:30,038
Mr. Lee is here.

279
00:15:30,038 --> 00:15:32,005
Who?

280
00:15:32,005 --> 00:15:33,338
How dare he come here?

281
00:15:33,338 --> 00:15:34,938
Then I'll send him back.

282
00:15:34,938 --> 00:15:37,772
No, send him in.

283
00:15:37,772 --> 00:15:39,472
Yes.

284
00:15:45,005 --> 00:15:47,738
I've committed an unforgivable sin.

285
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:50,272
Please forgive me just this once.

286
00:15:50,272 --> 00:15:51,905
How predictable.

287
00:15:51,905 --> 00:15:54,272
If you betrayed me for this,
I'm disappointed.

288
00:15:54,272 --> 00:15:55,305
I'll do anything.

289
00:15:55,305 --> 00:15:57,038
If you just let me redo the sculpture...

290
00:15:57,038 --> 00:15:58,672
A dog that bites its owner

291
00:15:58,672 --> 00:16:01,905
will bite again when cornered.

292
00:16:01,905 --> 00:16:03,605
Why should I give

293
00:16:03,605 --> 00:16:06,605
someone like you another chance?

294
00:16:08,372 --> 00:16:11,805
A dog only does what it's told, doesn't it?

295
00:16:11,805 --> 00:16:15,305
I'll prove I'm more than that.

296
00:16:15,305 --> 00:16:18,905
Now you sound like an artist. Interesting.

297
00:16:21,705 --> 00:16:24,672
Wait for my call.

298
00:16:24,672 --> 00:16:27,038
Go take a bath.

299
00:16:39,272 --> 00:16:42,272
Is it really right to keep going with this?

300
00:16:42,272 --> 00:16:43,305
Manager Jang.

301
00:16:43,305 --> 00:16:45,772
About next year's new product line...

302
00:16:50,338 --> 00:16:51,405
Manager.

303
00:16:51,405 --> 00:16:52,972
- What?
- Do you happen to have

304
00:16:52,972 --> 00:16:56,138
the file that summarizes the new product
lineup for the first half of next year?

305
00:16:56,138 --> 00:16:59,238
The team leader is looking for it,
but I haven't...

306
00:16:59,238 --> 00:17:01,305
- finished organizing it yet.
- Oh, that one?

307
00:17:01,305 --> 00:17:03,738
One moment.

308
00:17:03,738 --> 00:17:05,805
Here, this one.

309
00:17:05,805 --> 00:17:07,538
Thank you.

310
00:17:10,438 --> 00:17:12,205
Is something bothering you?

311
00:17:12,205 --> 00:17:14,838
You've been sighing nonstop since earlier.

312
00:17:14,838 --> 00:17:19,072
I'm just worried whether non-alcoholic beer
has real commercialization potential.

313
00:17:19,072 --> 00:17:21,872
Oh, because of the contest?

314
00:17:22,805 --> 00:17:24,005
It is challenging.

315
00:17:24,005 --> 00:17:26,805
Since it's non-alcoholic, it's hard
to be sure there'll be enough demand.

316
00:17:26,805 --> 00:17:30,138
So I'm seriously wondering
if I should switch to a different idea.

317
00:17:30,138 --> 00:17:34,138
But I tend to trust your instincts.

318
00:17:34,138 --> 00:17:36,293
- Pardon?
- Everything you've planned so far

319
00:17:36,293 --> 00:17:37,905
has been good.

320
00:17:37,905 --> 00:17:41,972
I think good products usually
start with wanting to solve

321
00:17:41,972 --> 00:17:44,172
someone's inconvenience.

322
00:17:44,172 --> 00:17:46,238
Like the Try Golden Ratio Glass.

323
00:17:46,238 --> 00:17:49,672
It was made for people
who struggle with mixing ratios.

324
00:17:49,672 --> 00:17:51,372
Right.

325
00:17:52,305 --> 00:17:53,905
- Wasn't it?
- And besides,

326
00:17:53,905 --> 00:17:57,772
isn't it your style to just go for it first?

327
00:17:57,772 --> 00:17:59,505
Assistant Manager Choi.

328
00:18:00,538 --> 00:18:01,705
Thank you.

329
00:18:01,705 --> 00:18:03,738
I really appreciate it too.

330
00:18:07,372 --> 00:18:11,572
The idea of wanting to solve
an inconvenience,

331
00:18:12,872 --> 00:18:17,305
and a beer people can enjoy
together in a healthy way.

332
00:18:18,738 --> 00:18:19,938
Huh? Non-alcoholic?

333
00:18:19,938 --> 00:18:23,605
So you're going for
non-alcoholic beer for the contest?

334
00:18:23,605 --> 00:18:25,305
Manager Nah's high-proof beer

335
00:18:25,305 --> 00:18:27,105
versus Manager Jang's non-alcoholic beer.

336
00:18:27,105 --> 00:18:28,938
You two are on total
opposite ends of the spectrum.

337
00:18:28,938 --> 00:18:31,072
Don't you know non-alcoholic
has limited market potential?

338
00:18:31,072 --> 00:18:32,938
Marketability is part
of the judging criteria.

339
00:18:32,938 --> 00:18:34,705
The global non-alcoholic beer market

340
00:18:34,705 --> 00:18:37,372
is growing 8 to 10% annually.

341
00:18:37,372 --> 00:18:40,905
Now's the chance to capture
the emerging market early.

342
00:18:40,905 --> 00:18:43,405
Come on, why drink if you
don't want to get drunk?

343
00:18:43,405 --> 00:18:47,738
Come on, so many young people
prioritize health nowadays.

344
00:18:47,738 --> 00:18:51,338
Thinking people drink just to get drunk
is such an old-school mindset.

345
00:18:51,338 --> 00:18:53,172
- Old-school.
- Among American youth,

346
00:18:53,172 --> 00:18:56,605
they say sober curious has become
a real social phenomenon.

347
00:18:56,605 --> 00:18:58,938
The culture of enjoying alcohol
without getting drunk is growing...

348
00:18:58,938 --> 00:19:00,905
Sober Mercury or whatever, I'm against it.

349
00:19:00,905 --> 00:19:02,138
Go ask around college campuses.

350
00:19:02,138 --> 00:19:04,005
Who prefers non-alcoholic over high-proof?

351
00:19:04,005 --> 00:19:05,872
Right, Assistant Manager Cha?

352
00:19:07,605 --> 00:19:10,138
What do you think?

353
00:19:10,138 --> 00:19:11,638
Well,

354
00:19:11,638 --> 00:19:14,005
from selling to various stores,

355
00:19:14,005 --> 00:19:16,605
both feasibility and marketability

356
00:19:16,605 --> 00:19:19,238
are far superior for high-proof beer.

357
00:19:20,005 --> 00:19:21,805
See?

358
00:19:22,572 --> 00:19:26,505
But if we were just going to go
with familiar, safe ideas,

359
00:19:26,505 --> 00:19:29,438
I don't think they'd bother
holding a contest like this.

360
00:19:29,438 --> 00:19:32,205
The whole point is
innovation and fresh ideas,

361
00:19:32,205 --> 00:19:33,805
so this is when we need
a differentiated perspective.

362
00:19:33,805 --> 00:19:36,538
No, innovation doesn't
mean unprofitable ideas.

363
00:19:36,538 --> 00:19:39,005
We won't know profitability until we try.

364
00:19:39,005 --> 00:19:40,905
I'll do market research by next week.

365
00:19:40,905 --> 00:19:42,238
All I need to do is prove

366
00:19:42,238 --> 00:19:44,572
whether non-alcoholic beer will resonate

367
00:19:44,572 --> 00:19:46,905
with young people or not, right?

368
00:19:52,605 --> 00:19:53,805
Would that be okay?

369
00:19:53,805 --> 00:19:58,405
I'm on your side, Manager, but my friends
might think differently, so...

370
00:19:58,405 --> 00:20:00,072
Then that's exactly what we need.

371
00:20:00,072 --> 00:20:01,772
Pardon?

372
00:20:02,472 --> 00:20:04,738
Manager Nah has a point.

373
00:20:04,738 --> 00:20:06,472
I acknowledge that somewhat.

374
00:20:06,472 --> 00:20:10,005
I've always heard 'it's impossible,'
now I'll show it works.

375
00:20:10,005 --> 00:20:11,438
The real question for me is

376
00:20:11,438 --> 00:20:13,538
what kind of non-alcoholic beer

377
00:20:13,538 --> 00:20:16,005
could actually change the market.

378
00:20:16,005 --> 00:20:18,472
Oh, Manager.

379
00:20:21,072 --> 00:20:22,772
Um, would you mind heading in first?

380
00:20:22,772 --> 00:20:25,138
I need to talk with Assistant Manager Cha.

381
00:20:25,138 --> 00:20:27,338
Oh, sure.

382
00:20:31,905 --> 00:20:35,572
Well, shall we talk for a moment?

383
00:20:42,705 --> 00:20:46,138
I have something to tell you.

384
00:20:48,105 --> 00:20:50,872
Can I go first?

385
00:20:50,872 --> 00:20:56,038
Have you talked with the President?
About the blind date.

386
00:20:56,038 --> 00:20:57,172
Why are you looking at me like that?

387
00:20:57,172 --> 00:20:58,805
Min Uk, you're so thoughtful.

388
00:20:58,805 --> 00:21:01,505
You're always kind to me.

389
00:21:01,505 --> 00:21:03,405
What's that mean? Of course I'd...

390
00:21:03,405 --> 00:21:05,038
It's not a given.

391
00:21:05,038 --> 00:21:09,538
Putting others before yourself
is incredibly hard.

392
00:21:11,072 --> 00:21:13,338
I think

393
00:21:13,338 --> 00:21:15,672
that might be why I liked you.

394
00:21:15,672 --> 00:21:16,772
Huh?

395
00:21:16,772 --> 00:21:18,405
But thinking back,

396
00:21:18,405 --> 00:21:23,438
I confused gratitude with romantic feelings.

397
00:21:23,438 --> 00:21:25,605
Actually,

398
00:21:25,605 --> 00:21:27,438
I went to his blind date.

399
00:21:27,438 --> 00:21:29,305
You went there?

400
00:21:29,305 --> 00:21:31,238
There was a misunderstanding.

401
00:21:31,238 --> 00:21:33,438
Before your call,

402
00:21:33,438 --> 00:21:36,605
I wasn't sure about my feelings.

403
00:21:36,605 --> 00:21:39,838
But once I heard about the blind date,
that's when I realized it.

404
00:21:42,905 --> 00:21:45,672
I like the President.

405
00:21:45,672 --> 00:21:49,038
Sorry, I can't give the answer you want.

406
00:21:52,905 --> 00:21:55,038
- I knew it.
- Huh?

407
00:21:55,038 --> 00:21:57,238
I've known you for years.

408
00:21:57,238 --> 00:22:01,072
I didn't confess to you
without being prepared for this much.

409
00:22:01,072 --> 00:22:03,538
And I don't think this is over yet.

410
00:22:03,538 --> 00:22:07,038
- Min Uk.
- I want to see this through.

411
00:22:07,038 --> 00:22:10,905
So please don't cut it off so decisively.

412
00:22:13,638 --> 00:22:15,372
I'll go ahead.

413
00:22:39,397 --> 00:22:41,061
Oh.

414
00:22:42,277 --> 00:22:45,538
It seems you basically handles
all the work around here.

415
00:22:45,538 --> 00:22:47,338
President.

416
00:22:47,338 --> 00:22:48,905
Why? Is something wrong?

417
00:22:48,905 --> 00:22:50,738
You don't look well.

418
00:22:50,738 --> 00:22:54,638
No, it's just that I have a lot on my plate,
and my belly keeps growing.

419
00:22:54,638 --> 00:22:56,472
I'm starting to feel a bit pressed.

420
00:22:56,472 --> 00:22:57,972
Even when handing things over,

421
00:22:57,972 --> 00:23:01,238
I want to make it easy
for the next person to follow.

422
00:23:01,238 --> 00:23:02,438
- That's cool.
- Huh?

423
00:23:02,438 --> 00:23:03,572
I mean, you are cool.

424
00:23:03,572 --> 00:23:06,438
Your passion for work, and the way
you think about your coworkers.

425
00:23:06,438 --> 00:23:09,405
Wait, you just realized that now?

426
00:23:09,405 --> 00:23:11,205
I guess so.

427
00:23:13,405 --> 00:23:15,905
If I wanted to know more, what should I do?

428
00:23:24,005 --> 00:23:25,372
What? Is someone there?

429
00:23:25,372 --> 00:23:26,672
There shouldn't be anyone here.

430
00:23:26,672 --> 00:23:28,805
Quick, hide!

431
00:23:28,805 --> 00:23:30,572
Over there, over there.

432
00:23:31,905 --> 00:23:35,505
But if any employee is here at this hour...
There shouldn't be anyone.

433
00:23:35,505 --> 00:23:38,338
Don't worry. I've confirmed everyone left.

434
00:23:38,338 --> 00:23:41,572
Then, would you like to eat in my office?

435
00:23:41,572 --> 00:23:42,605
Shall we?

436
00:23:42,605 --> 00:23:45,372
Team Leader Bang and Secretary Go?

437
00:23:45,372 --> 00:23:47,072
Hold on.

438
00:23:47,072 --> 00:23:50,605
What's this smell? Smells delicious.

439
00:23:53,772 --> 00:23:55,272
What smell could it be?

440
00:23:55,272 --> 00:23:57,772
It's the smell of my heart burning.

441
00:23:57,772 --> 00:24:00,505
I'm hungry. Let's go in and eat.

442
00:24:00,505 --> 00:24:02,205
Noona.

443
00:24:06,341 --> 00:24:09,338
Oh, noona.

444
00:24:09,338 --> 00:24:11,438
So he's dating Team Leader Bang?
Just the two of them?

445
00:24:11,438 --> 00:24:12,672
He's finally gone crazy.

446
00:24:12,672 --> 00:24:14,372
Oh my, oh my.

447
00:24:16,105 --> 00:24:18,072
It's now. Get out quickly.

448
00:24:18,072 --> 00:24:20,572
Seriously...

449
00:24:21,272 --> 00:24:23,372
[Requesting a driver within 12 minutes]

450
00:24:27,372 --> 00:24:28,438
No taxis around.

451
00:24:28,438 --> 00:24:30,072
I can't get one on the app either.

452
00:24:30,072 --> 00:24:32,538
I should've just gone to get the car keys.

453
00:24:32,538 --> 00:24:35,638
Even so, they seem to be on a date.
Let's not get in the way.

454
00:24:35,638 --> 00:24:36,972
Jeez.

455
00:24:36,972 --> 00:24:38,772
Still, if you catch a cold...

456
00:24:38,772 --> 00:24:40,772
This won't do. I'll just call
Secretary Go to bring the car now.

457
00:24:40,772 --> 00:24:42,738
No, please don't.

458
00:24:49,938 --> 00:24:51,638
Oh, a taxi's here.

459
00:24:55,705 --> 00:24:58,005
- Get in.
- Should I go?

460
00:24:58,005 --> 00:25:00,238
I still have work to finish.

461
00:25:00,238 --> 00:25:01,838
Please make sure she gets home safely.

462
00:25:01,838 --> 00:25:02,938
Okay.

463
00:25:02,938 --> 00:25:05,772
- President.
- Call me when you get home.

464
00:25:31,738 --> 00:25:33,138
President, wait.

465
00:25:33,138 --> 00:25:35,705
- I'll call Secretary Go to bring the car.
- No, please don't.

466
00:25:37,072 --> 00:25:39,638
Am I being too sensitive?

467
00:25:50,597 --> 00:25:52,229
Ugh.

468
00:25:53,938 --> 00:25:58,005
Of all people, a blind date
with the Taehan Liquor President?

469
00:25:58,005 --> 00:26:00,105
Does Hui Won know about this too?

470
00:26:00,105 --> 00:26:02,572
Should I tell her, or not?

471
00:26:03,572 --> 00:26:05,172
Huh?

472
00:26:05,172 --> 00:26:06,438
- Jang Hui Won.
- What?

473
00:26:06,438 --> 00:26:07,905
Why are you here, Hui Won?

474
00:26:07,905 --> 00:26:10,772
What? She knew everything already.

475
00:26:13,805 --> 00:26:15,872
Does Min Uk know?

476
00:26:20,613 --> 00:26:21,972
[Hangover Remedy]
Jeez.

477
00:26:21,972 --> 00:26:24,172
I'm in no position to worry about anyone.

478
00:26:36,005 --> 00:26:37,938
Honestly, I regretted it the whole way home.

479
00:26:37,938 --> 00:26:39,372
I shouldn't have stepped aside.

480
00:26:39,372 --> 00:26:40,405
Is something wrong?

481
00:26:40,405 --> 00:26:41,538
You've been acting strange lately.

482
00:26:41,538 --> 00:26:43,672
You keep acting childish
while competing with the President.

483
00:26:43,672 --> 00:26:45,305
Even had a pride contest over drinks.

484
00:26:45,305 --> 00:26:48,238
Do you really not know why I'm like this?

485
00:26:51,305 --> 00:26:52,905
Did she dump you?

486
00:26:52,905 --> 00:26:57,272
You reminded me of myself, the way
I used to drink after I broke up.

487
00:26:58,305 --> 00:27:01,105
- Why are you here?
- The owner called me.

488
00:27:01,105 --> 00:27:04,238
She said my friend is here, moping alone.

489
00:27:05,505 --> 00:27:07,638
Just kidding. She told me
to come take care of you.

490
00:27:07,638 --> 00:27:09,938
She asked why the three of us
haven't been hanging out lately.

491
00:27:16,938 --> 00:27:19,905
Are you disappointed it's not Hui Won?

492
00:27:24,738 --> 00:27:26,805
It's not that.

493
00:27:28,072 --> 00:27:32,238
I just feel like I had so many chances,
and I let them all slip away.

494
00:27:33,505 --> 00:27:37,105
I thought courage was only
needed to confess your feelings.

495
00:27:37,938 --> 00:27:40,293
But it turns out,

496
00:27:40,293 --> 00:27:42,905
being rejected takes courage too.

497
00:27:42,905 --> 00:27:44,538
You're amazing, Hwang Mi Ran.

498
00:27:44,538 --> 00:27:47,205
You're much braver than I am.

499
00:27:47,205 --> 00:27:49,438
You just realized that now?

500
00:27:50,472 --> 00:27:52,238
Maybe I'm just being stupidly naive.

501
00:27:52,238 --> 00:27:54,405
Why did I even come back here?

502
00:27:59,572 --> 00:28:02,438
I know you're naive.

503
00:28:02,438 --> 00:28:04,405
- What?
- I mean, why did you come here?

504
00:28:04,405 --> 00:28:05,972
What did you expect to see?

505
00:28:05,972 --> 00:28:09,905
I came to see you all disheveled like a mess.

506
00:28:09,905 --> 00:28:10,938
Did you come for revenge?

507
00:28:10,938 --> 00:28:13,272
Yeah, but don't get me wrong.

508
00:28:13,272 --> 00:28:16,172
Today, I'm not Hwang Mi Ran who likes you.

509
00:28:16,172 --> 00:28:18,538
I came as your friend Hwang Mi Ran.

510
00:28:18,538 --> 00:28:21,538
Just for today, as a friend,
I'll listen to everything.

511
00:28:21,538 --> 00:28:22,938
Just like you always did for me.

512
00:28:22,938 --> 00:28:24,938
So don't drink alone.

513
00:28:24,938 --> 00:28:26,938
I'm upset.

514
00:28:53,272 --> 00:28:55,672
Seriously, did I just send
a pregnant woman off in a taxi?

515
00:28:55,672 --> 00:28:57,538
And why did I pull my hand away there?

516
00:28:57,538 --> 00:28:59,472
Jeez.

517
00:29:03,972 --> 00:29:06,405
She must be so disappointed.

518
00:29:06,405 --> 00:29:11,505
I should've taken her home,
or at least shared the taxi with her.

519
00:29:13,093 --> 00:29:14,751
Jeez.

520
00:29:19,077 --> 00:29:21,338
She hasn't even contacted me.

521
00:29:22,138 --> 00:29:24,938
I wonder if she got home safely.

522
00:29:24,938 --> 00:29:26,972
She couldn't be sulking, could she?

523
00:29:27,805 --> 00:29:30,938
Ugh, after leaving like that,
I'd be upset too if I were her.

524
00:29:32,472 --> 00:29:36,138
Well, I can make it up to her.

525
00:29:36,138 --> 00:29:41,672
Finding great restaurants
and planning date routes is my specialty.

526
00:29:41,672 --> 00:29:46,605
Cultural stuff, performances, exhibitions,
then a date that flows smoothly

527
00:29:46,605 --> 00:29:49,172
into a nearby restaurant,
a cafe, and a walking path.

528
00:29:49,172 --> 00:29:50,605
If she wants something more active,

529
00:29:50,605 --> 00:29:52,872
[A park or near the Han River]
head to an open park or near the Han River,

530
00:29:52,872 --> 00:29:54,742
hop on a bike, and just ride.

531
00:29:54,742 --> 00:29:57,338
The view's nice. Take pictures there.

532
00:29:57,338 --> 00:29:59,805
Ah, but Hui Won might not be up for that.

533
00:29:59,805 --> 00:30:01,272
Well, then.

534
00:30:01,272 --> 00:30:03,105
Oh! A food-focused date.

535
00:30:03,105 --> 00:30:04,972
[A foodie date]
How about a foodie date?

536
00:30:04,972 --> 00:30:06,072
Ah, no.

537
00:30:06,072 --> 00:30:07,438
You know, something women love.

538
00:30:07,438 --> 00:30:09,205
[Shopping]
Shopping. Yeah, shopping.

539
00:30:09,205 --> 00:30:12,738
Starting light with shopping isn't
a bad idea either. Yeah, that should work.

540
00:30:12,738 --> 00:30:14,838
Your answers just flow out like rap.

541
00:30:14,838 --> 00:30:18,172
I told you, it's my specialty.

542
00:30:20,405 --> 00:30:23,372
So which one do you like best?

543
00:30:26,005 --> 00:30:27,805
Let's go on a date today.

544
00:30:27,805 --> 00:30:29,472
I'll come pick you up
at your place by eleven.

545
00:30:29,472 --> 00:30:32,772
This one looks like it might be
tight around the waist too.

546
00:30:37,838 --> 00:30:41,705
When did this get so small?

547
00:30:44,438 --> 00:30:48,372
Do I need to start buying
maternity clothes soon?

548
00:31:06,238 --> 00:31:08,405
Let's go.

549
00:31:08,405 --> 00:31:10,138
Yes.

550
00:31:12,105 --> 00:31:14,605
These are our new arrivals.

551
00:31:14,605 --> 00:31:17,772
I've got several laid out, so pick one.

552
00:31:17,772 --> 00:31:19,272
This one and this one.

553
00:31:19,272 --> 00:31:20,972
- This one and...
- Pick a few more.

554
00:31:20,972 --> 00:31:23,105
The pink one.

555
00:31:32,538 --> 00:31:34,872
- This one is really pretty.
- Jeez.

556
00:31:34,872 --> 00:31:37,205
Right? Isn't she pretty?

557
00:31:37,205 --> 00:31:39,872
Please don't.

558
00:31:41,138 --> 00:31:44,172
Huh? It's been a while.

559
00:31:46,372 --> 00:31:48,772
- Brother-in-law?
- What, brother-in-law?

560
00:31:48,772 --> 00:31:50,138
Then you and President are...

561
00:31:50,138 --> 00:31:51,205
You two know each other?

562
00:31:51,205 --> 00:31:53,905
Ah, we ran into each other
at my regular spot.

563
00:31:53,905 --> 00:31:55,638
By chance?

564
00:31:57,805 --> 00:31:59,505
Secretary Yoon.

565
00:32:01,605 --> 00:32:04,538
So the person you are seeing

566
00:32:04,538 --> 00:32:05,572
is Hui Won?

567
00:32:05,572 --> 00:32:08,972
Oh my, are we going to be family soon?

568
00:32:08,972 --> 00:32:11,605
Well then, why not just
come and greet the family?

569
00:32:11,605 --> 00:32:12,938
Mother and Father,

570
00:32:12,938 --> 00:32:15,972
if they hear you are the person
he is marrying, they'd be delighted.

571
00:32:15,972 --> 00:32:17,405
We'll handle that ourselves.

572
00:32:17,405 --> 00:32:19,805
Why, if she's a woman you brought,

573
00:32:19,805 --> 00:32:23,338
even my late husband would have liked her.

574
00:32:24,372 --> 00:32:27,738
Oh, can you actually hold hands now?

575
00:32:27,738 --> 00:32:29,438
Jeong Eum.

576
00:32:30,838 --> 00:32:32,872
Stop this.

577
00:32:32,872 --> 00:32:34,505
We'll head out first.

578
00:32:34,505 --> 00:32:36,305
Let's go.

579
00:32:46,738 --> 00:32:50,138
Does he even realize his wallet's missing?

580
00:32:51,372 --> 00:32:55,405
Not a single call, and making me
wait all the time.

581
00:32:57,605 --> 00:32:58,672
Oh, Dad.

582
00:32:58,672 --> 00:33:00,238
You're getting off work soon, right?

583
00:33:00,238 --> 00:33:01,472
Yeah, a little later.

584
00:33:01,472 --> 00:33:03,472
Did you call to ask about that?

585
00:33:03,472 --> 00:33:05,105
Oh no, that's not it.

586
00:33:05,105 --> 00:33:08,138
Hey, are you free tomorrow?

587
00:33:08,138 --> 00:33:11,238
Huh? What is it? This feels really familiar.

588
00:33:11,238 --> 00:33:14,005
I've arranged an absolutely
amazing blind date.

589
00:33:14,005 --> 00:33:15,538
Just go for it once.

590
00:33:15,538 --> 00:33:17,805
Just do it. No questions.

591
00:33:18,472 --> 00:33:22,405
Dad, after what happened
last time, another blind date?

592
00:33:22,405 --> 00:33:24,305
I'm not doing it, really not doing it.

593
00:33:24,305 --> 00:33:27,405
Come on, you know last time
doesn't count, right?

594
00:33:27,405 --> 00:33:30,138
This time it's not just good conditions.

595
00:33:30,138 --> 00:33:34,372
Good conditions plus a really nice person.

596
00:33:34,372 --> 00:33:36,672
You know your dad has
high standards for people, right?

597
00:33:36,672 --> 00:33:40,605
Enough. If you keep talking like that,
I'm hanging up. I'm busy. Goodbye.

598
00:33:41,338 --> 00:33:43,972
Ah, enough with the blind dates.

599
00:33:43,972 --> 00:33:46,338
I prefer to meet people naturally.

600
00:33:49,072 --> 00:33:50,172
Alright.

601
00:33:50,172 --> 00:33:53,472
I'll find someone who likes me for me.

602
00:33:59,505 --> 00:34:01,605
Is something going on between those two?

603
00:34:01,605 --> 00:34:05,072
Her late husband, that would be
the President's brother?

604
00:34:05,072 --> 00:34:08,238
But what does that have to do
with the hand-holding?

605
00:34:10,538 --> 00:34:12,172
Wow, I...

606
00:34:12,172 --> 00:34:16,505
I truly never imagined you two were family.

607
00:34:16,505 --> 00:34:20,472
So that means she's Se Hyeon's mom?

608
00:34:20,472 --> 00:34:23,505
Ah, what a small world.

609
00:34:23,505 --> 00:34:26,805
Now that you mention it
they do resemble each other a bit.

610
00:34:31,205 --> 00:34:33,238
President.

611
00:34:33,238 --> 00:34:35,972
- Yes?
- Are you okay?

612
00:34:35,972 --> 00:34:38,272
What? I'm fine.

613
00:34:38,272 --> 00:34:40,172
Eat quickly, it's getting cold.

614
00:34:40,172 --> 00:34:41,938
Yes.

615
00:34:45,238 --> 00:34:48,672
So when did you first meet my sister-in-law?

616
00:34:48,672 --> 00:34:50,872
The first time?

617
00:34:50,872 --> 00:34:52,705
Uh...

618
00:34:52,705 --> 00:34:53,838
Well...

619
00:34:53,838 --> 00:34:55,338
Ah! That day.

620
00:34:55,338 --> 00:34:57,905
The day I confirmed my pregnancy
at that hospital.

621
00:34:57,905 --> 00:35:00,672
Then how many times have you met?

622
00:35:00,672 --> 00:35:02,238
When and where?

623
00:35:02,238 --> 00:35:05,072
Why are you asking?

624
00:35:05,072 --> 00:35:06,538
Just curious.

625
00:35:06,538 --> 00:35:08,705
Don't overthink it, just eat.

626
00:35:24,372 --> 00:35:26,272
The date ended so quick.

627
00:35:26,272 --> 00:35:28,372
What's your purpose
in approaching Jang Hui Won?

628
00:35:28,372 --> 00:35:31,205
Didn't I already say I'd give
Taehan Group to Se Hyeon?

629
00:35:31,205 --> 00:35:33,105
Purpose?

630
00:35:33,105 --> 00:35:35,205
I already said it was a coincidence earlier.

631
00:35:35,205 --> 00:35:38,305
If you touch Jang Hui Won,
I won't hold back anymore.

632
00:35:38,305 --> 00:35:41,405
Is that how someone who promised
Taehan Group behaves?

633
00:35:41,405 --> 00:35:43,538
You're still acting like this.

634
00:35:43,538 --> 00:35:46,038
How can I trust you?

635
00:35:48,938 --> 00:35:53,472
Do you still blame me for my brother's death?

636
00:35:53,472 --> 00:35:56,872
Because of the guilt I felt,
I've lived the way you wanted.

637
00:35:56,872 --> 00:36:01,105
I just did the basics without greed,
taking over what my brother wanted to do.

638
00:36:01,105 --> 00:36:04,238
Even so, what are you so afraid of?

639
00:36:04,238 --> 00:36:06,205
You were the one who crossed the line.

640
00:36:06,205 --> 00:36:09,872
Now I'll protect my loved ones too.

641
00:36:10,872 --> 00:36:12,705
I'm curious.

642
00:36:14,872 --> 00:36:16,338
I'll be looking forward to it.

643
00:36:16,338 --> 00:36:19,772
You'll have to do your best to protect them.

644
00:36:27,272 --> 00:36:29,738
Oh, Professor Lee, nice to see you.

645
00:36:29,738 --> 00:36:33,205
Professor Lee, why is it so hard
to have one meal together?

646
00:36:33,205 --> 00:36:35,272
- Well...
- Let's meet more often.

647
00:36:35,272 --> 00:36:38,872
We're not going to put up walls
just because you're a lecturer.

648
00:36:38,872 --> 00:36:40,272
Yes.

649
00:36:40,272 --> 00:36:43,838
Well, my eldest son
is getting married this time.

650
00:36:43,838 --> 00:36:45,672
So I wanted to treat you to a meal.

651
00:36:45,672 --> 00:36:46,838
Make some time.

652
00:36:46,838 --> 00:36:49,438
Oh, Professor, congratulations.

653
00:36:49,438 --> 00:36:51,572
People these days
aren't getting married much.

654
00:36:51,572 --> 00:36:52,672
Exactly.

655
00:36:52,672 --> 00:36:55,738
We've been worried about
non-marriage and stuff,

656
00:36:55,738 --> 00:36:57,905
and now he's finally getting married.

657
00:36:57,905 --> 00:36:59,672
Not marrying is a problem,

658
00:36:59,672 --> 00:37:02,972
but meeting people and breaking up
too easily is also a big issue.

659
00:37:02,972 --> 00:37:06,372
They divorce like it's nothing.

660
00:37:06,372 --> 00:37:08,938
And what about those
who have shotgun weddings?

661
00:37:08,938 --> 00:37:12,338
These days, they don't even
consider that a big deal.

662
00:37:12,338 --> 00:37:14,472
What is the world coming to?

663
00:37:14,472 --> 00:37:17,705
We need to keep a close eye on the kids.

664
00:37:17,705 --> 00:37:21,372
But is that really that bad?

665
00:37:23,705 --> 00:37:26,205
If they don't take responsibility, then yes.

666
00:37:29,338 --> 00:37:30,672
That's right, but...

667
00:37:30,672 --> 00:37:33,738
Whether it's shotgun weddings or divorce,
they're paths people choose.

668
00:37:33,738 --> 00:37:38,272
Having others judge that recklessly feels

669
00:37:38,272 --> 00:37:39,372
not right, I think.

670
00:37:39,372 --> 00:37:42,472
Well, Professor Lee has a point.

671
00:37:42,472 --> 00:37:43,572
Right?

672
00:37:43,572 --> 00:37:46,005
Professor, I'm really looking forward to it.

673
00:37:46,005 --> 00:37:48,338
Where are we going this time?

674
00:37:57,405 --> 00:38:01,438
Seriously, just looking at the steak,
and now ramyeon?

675
00:38:08,205 --> 00:38:11,338
I don't think he even got to eat much.

676
00:38:13,472 --> 00:38:17,005
[President Kang Du Jun]

677
00:38:25,072 --> 00:38:26,105
Yes, President.

678
00:38:26,105 --> 00:38:28,638
- What are you doing?
- Well...

679
00:38:29,305 --> 00:38:31,638
[Growing Hops Malts]
Rea... reading.

680
00:38:31,638 --> 00:38:32,638
Reading?

681
00:38:32,638 --> 00:38:34,505
Yes, as a hobby.

682
00:38:34,505 --> 00:38:39,238
When I find parts I like while reading,
I scrapbook them.

683
00:38:40,505 --> 00:38:42,872
Anyway, sorry for
sending you home so suddenly.

684
00:38:42,872 --> 00:38:44,672
Something urgent came up.

685
00:38:44,672 --> 00:38:46,638
It's okay, don't worry about it.

686
00:38:46,638 --> 00:38:48,305
I just felt bad, that's why.

687
00:38:48,305 --> 00:38:50,905
It was our first date
since we started dating.

688
00:38:52,172 --> 00:38:55,938
President, are you the type to read
too much into things like that?

689
00:38:55,938 --> 00:38:57,872
Absolutely, I really read
too much into things.

690
00:38:57,872 --> 00:38:59,572
So let's just void this one.

691
00:38:59,572 --> 00:39:01,738
- Void?
- Just name anywhere you want to go.

692
00:39:01,738 --> 00:39:03,472
I'll prepare properly next time.

693
00:39:03,472 --> 00:39:05,805
You mean

694
00:39:05,805 --> 00:39:06,905
anywhere?

695
00:39:06,905 --> 00:39:08,372
Hurry up!

696
00:39:08,372 --> 00:39:09,905
- No, this place is...
- Quickly.

697
00:39:09,905 --> 00:39:12,472
I said hurry up.

698
00:39:12,472 --> 00:39:13,938
Ta-da!

699
00:39:13,938 --> 00:39:17,005
I told you to pick wherever you want,
but why an amusement park?

700
00:39:17,005 --> 00:39:18,372
You probably can't even ride properly.

701
00:39:18,372 --> 00:39:20,705
I only come here for the churros, you know?

702
00:39:20,705 --> 00:39:22,438
No time. Let's go, quick.

703
00:39:22,438 --> 00:39:25,472
- Quick, quick!
- Why eat churros here?

704
00:39:26,981 --> 00:39:28,072
Hey!

705
00:39:28,072 --> 00:39:29,205
I don't wear headbands like this.

706
00:39:29,205 --> 00:39:31,238
This one, this one.

707
00:39:31,238 --> 00:39:32,938
This is better.

708
00:39:34,438 --> 00:39:36,505
But isn't this so exciting?

709
00:39:36,505 --> 00:39:38,905
The weather's perfect too.

710
00:39:38,905 --> 00:39:40,838
Do you like it that much?

711
00:39:40,838 --> 00:39:42,572
Yes.

712
00:39:44,472 --> 00:39:46,205
Crazy.

713
00:39:46,205 --> 00:39:47,438
You really can't ride that.

714
00:39:47,438 --> 00:39:50,372
I know. Who even rides that?

715
00:39:51,038 --> 00:39:52,972
Wow.

716
00:39:52,972 --> 00:39:55,538
Then I'll take this one.

717
00:39:58,505 --> 00:40:00,405
Why am I riding this?

718
00:40:00,405 --> 00:40:02,538
President! President!

719
00:40:02,538 --> 00:40:03,838
Look here!

720
00:40:03,838 --> 00:40:05,205
President!

721
00:40:05,205 --> 00:40:08,072
Look here, over here!

722
00:40:23,772 --> 00:40:25,572
Thank you.

723
00:40:27,838 --> 00:40:29,272
- Yum.
- Is it delicious?

724
00:40:29,272 --> 00:40:30,672
Yes.

725
00:40:30,672 --> 00:40:32,838
Slow down, you'll get indigestion.

726
00:40:34,072 --> 00:40:36,238
You got it all over your lips.

727
00:41:00,605 --> 00:41:03,072
Wow, there's something
really pretty over there.

728
00:41:03,072 --> 00:41:05,072
Let's go.

729
00:41:16,772 --> 00:41:19,372
- I don't have to ride.
- It's fun to ride together.

730
00:41:19,372 --> 00:41:22,572
This is actually my first time on a carousel.

731
00:41:22,572 --> 00:41:26,672
I never went to amusement parks
with my family as a kid.

732
00:41:26,672 --> 00:41:29,938
Later with friends,
I mostly rode extreme rides.

733
00:41:29,938 --> 00:41:33,638
Ah, thanks to our Yeol Mu,
I finally get to ride this.

734
00:41:33,638 --> 00:41:36,138
Wow, this is fun.

735
00:41:38,772 --> 00:41:40,038
Why are you waving your hand?

736
00:41:40,038 --> 00:41:42,338
It's customary to wave
when you're on a carousel.

737
00:41:42,338 --> 00:41:44,638
People take pictures, you know.

738
00:41:52,072 --> 00:41:53,872
Get off carefully.

739
00:42:04,938 --> 00:42:07,172
Why won't you hold my hand?

740
00:42:09,029 --> 00:42:10,605
Oh.

741
00:42:10,605 --> 00:42:14,238
- Well...
- Please exit safely.

742
00:42:16,038 --> 00:42:17,772
They're telling us to exit.

743
00:42:26,738 --> 00:42:28,872
I've heard a lot about you from the director.

744
00:42:28,872 --> 00:42:30,772
At the company, he constantly
brags about you, Mi Ran.

745
00:42:30,772 --> 00:42:32,672
He says you're such a kind daughter.

746
00:42:34,605 --> 00:42:35,738
Here, use this.

747
00:42:35,738 --> 00:42:38,238
Yes, thank you.

748
00:42:39,205 --> 00:42:41,138
Did my dad really say that?

749
00:42:41,138 --> 00:42:42,772
- Yes.
- That doesn't sound like him.

750
00:42:42,772 --> 00:42:45,138
I asked the director first

751
00:42:45,138 --> 00:42:46,538
if I could meet you, Mi Ran.

752
00:42:46,538 --> 00:42:49,005
Thank you so much for coming again.

753
00:42:49,005 --> 00:42:50,738
Not at all.

754
00:42:50,738 --> 00:42:52,705
Now, I too,

755
00:42:52,705 --> 00:42:56,805
want to meet someone who likes me.

756
00:43:03,738 --> 00:43:05,872
Use this.

757
00:43:05,872 --> 00:43:08,372
Have some cake too.

758
00:43:08,372 --> 00:43:12,772
What? He's so considerate and sweet.

759
00:43:12,772 --> 00:43:14,538
Just like Cha Min Uk.

760
00:43:14,538 --> 00:43:17,238
Mi Ran, enjoy your meal.

761
00:43:20,738 --> 00:43:23,972
Mi Ran! Mi Ran!

762
00:43:26,572 --> 00:43:29,005
- Mi Ran?
- Yes?

763
00:43:29,005 --> 00:43:30,738
Ah, I'm sorry. What did you say?

764
00:43:30,738 --> 00:43:32,838
Please tell me everything you like, Mi Ran.

765
00:43:32,838 --> 00:43:34,972
Favorite foods, hobbies.

766
00:43:34,972 --> 00:43:37,172
I want to know it all.

767
00:43:37,172 --> 00:43:38,872
What you enjoy.

768
00:43:38,872 --> 00:43:40,538
Oh, me?

769
00:43:40,538 --> 00:43:43,205
I like a lot of things.

770
00:43:43,205 --> 00:43:44,938
I like shopping,

771
00:43:44,938 --> 00:43:48,238
and I love eating delicious food.

772
00:43:51,605 --> 00:43:53,172
I'll walk you home.

773
00:43:53,172 --> 00:43:55,072
If that's uncomfortable, at least nearby.

774
00:43:55,072 --> 00:43:56,072
No need.

775
00:43:56,072 --> 00:43:58,405
It looked like something
urgent came up at work.

776
00:43:58,405 --> 00:43:59,405
You should go check quickly.

777
00:43:59,405 --> 00:44:02,505
It's not as urgent as walking you home.

778
00:44:02,505 --> 00:44:03,638
I'm really fine.

779
00:44:03,638 --> 00:44:05,838
I'll get home quickly if I take a taxi.

780
00:44:08,672 --> 00:44:10,805
Then let's go shopping together next time.

781
00:44:10,805 --> 00:44:14,572
I'll definitely walk you home then.

782
00:44:15,338 --> 00:44:16,838
Take care.

783
00:44:16,838 --> 00:44:18,538
Yes.

784
00:44:28,672 --> 00:44:30,338
He's a really good person.

785
00:44:30,338 --> 00:44:33,338
Wow, everything about him is great.
But he's not Cha Min Uk.

786
00:44:33,338 --> 00:44:36,038
I guess I just like Cha Min Uk.

787
00:44:37,572 --> 00:44:39,772
If it's not Cha Min Uk,

788
00:44:40,538 --> 00:44:42,638
it just doesn't work.

789
00:44:55,038 --> 00:44:57,405
And what about those
who have shotgun weddings?

790
00:44:57,405 --> 00:45:00,238
These days, they don't even
consider that a big deal.

791
00:45:00,238 --> 00:45:02,205
What is the world coming to?

792
00:45:02,205 --> 00:45:05,738
We need to keep a close eye on the kids.

793
00:45:08,197 --> 00:45:10,021
Jeez.

794
00:45:16,305 --> 00:45:18,693
[Hui Won]

795
00:45:21,072 --> 00:45:23,005
The subscriber you are calling
is not available.

796
00:45:23,005 --> 00:45:26,205
What could she be doing at this hour?

797
00:45:26,205 --> 00:45:27,505
And she's with child.

798
00:45:27,505 --> 00:45:28,901
[Hui Won]

799
00:45:30,838 --> 00:45:32,838
The subscriber you are calling
is not available.

800
00:45:32,838 --> 00:45:35,805
She doesn't even realize
I said that for her own good.

801
00:45:38,105 --> 00:45:41,272
Now she won't even talk to me? What is this?

802
00:45:53,305 --> 00:45:55,238
But your hand...

803
00:45:55,238 --> 00:45:57,138
Aren't you tired?

804
00:45:58,005 --> 00:45:59,405
I'm okay.

805
00:45:59,405 --> 00:46:01,805
It was fun getting some fresh air
after a while.

806
00:46:01,805 --> 00:46:04,938
- But President...
- The food there wasn't great earlier.

807
00:46:04,938 --> 00:46:07,238
I wanted to treat you to something delicious.

808
00:46:07,972 --> 00:46:10,305
It was fine.

809
00:46:13,038 --> 00:46:15,338
I'm getting tired now.

810
00:46:15,338 --> 00:46:16,838
I should go home and rest.

811
00:46:16,838 --> 00:46:18,638
Oh? Then get some rest now.

812
00:46:18,638 --> 00:46:20,772
I'll wake you when we get there.

813
00:46:50,638 --> 00:46:52,838
Why do you keep avoiding my hand?

814
00:46:52,838 --> 00:46:54,805
- Huh?
- My hand.

815
00:46:54,805 --> 00:46:57,272
You keep avoiding it.

816
00:46:57,272 --> 00:46:59,438
- It's not...
- I'm not saying this to you in a bad way.

817
00:46:59,438 --> 00:47:00,772
I just don't want to get the wrong idea.

818
00:47:00,772 --> 00:47:04,038
I need to know so I can help or understand.

819
00:47:04,038 --> 00:47:06,038
Is there a reason?

820
00:47:06,838 --> 00:47:09,172
A reason why you can't hold hands?

821
00:47:10,838 --> 00:47:12,272
President!

822
00:47:12,272 --> 00:47:14,605
Why aren't you answering your phone?

823
00:47:14,605 --> 00:47:16,538
Oh, Mom.

824
00:47:16,538 --> 00:47:19,272
And you said 'President'?

825
00:47:20,072 --> 00:47:22,738
Nice to meet you. My name is Kang Du Jun.

826
00:47:22,738 --> 00:47:25,572
This is the person I mentioned.

827
00:47:27,572 --> 00:47:30,638
Wait, so the man who got you pregnant

828
00:47:30,638 --> 00:47:31,905
is the President at your company?

829
00:47:31,905 --> 00:47:33,738
I was just about to tell you.

830
00:47:33,738 --> 00:47:35,272
What do you expect to do now?

831
00:47:35,272 --> 00:47:36,872
Are you just playing around with an employee?

832
00:47:36,872 --> 00:47:40,405
Surely you're not thinking of
just throwing money at this later, right?

833
00:47:40,405 --> 00:47:41,705
Just because you're the President,
does that make it okay?

834
00:47:41,705 --> 00:47:42,872
Mother, first of all, I'm truly sorry.

835
00:47:42,872 --> 00:47:44,105
Don't call me that!

836
00:47:44,105 --> 00:47:46,438
Mom, please calm down.

837
00:47:46,438 --> 00:47:47,605
You're just the same.

838
00:47:47,605 --> 00:47:49,238
Do you even have a plan?

839
00:47:49,238 --> 00:47:52,805
If people find out,
how are you going to deal with it?

840
00:47:52,805 --> 00:47:54,638
Is that why you said you won't get married?

841
00:47:54,638 --> 00:47:57,438
Because it's obvious
his family would oppose it?

842
00:47:57,438 --> 00:48:01,172
Why did you let things
get this far, you idiot!

843
00:48:01,172 --> 00:48:02,538
Please stop.

844
00:48:02,538 --> 00:48:04,572
How far are you going to embarrass me?

845
00:48:04,572 --> 00:48:06,405
You told me it's my life
and to live it my way,

846
00:48:06,405 --> 00:48:08,605
regret it, cry myself sick, whatever!

847
00:48:08,605 --> 00:48:10,072
You said you'd keep it no matter what.

848
00:48:10,072 --> 00:48:11,372
You said you won't get married!

849
00:48:11,372 --> 00:48:14,372
Then what on earth are you going to do?

850
00:48:14,372 --> 00:48:16,372
Do you think raising a child alone is easy?

851
00:48:16,372 --> 00:48:18,038
- Is raising a child a joke?
- I also...

852
00:48:18,038 --> 00:48:19,605
I also want to get married.

853
00:48:19,605 --> 00:48:21,472
Do you know why I said
I wouldn't get married?

854
00:48:21,472 --> 00:48:25,672
Do you think I don't want
a normal family like everyone else?

855
00:48:25,672 --> 00:48:27,572
It's all because of you, Mom.

856
00:48:27,572 --> 00:48:30,872
You never showed me a single day
of happiness after you got married.

857
00:48:30,872 --> 00:48:33,738
How could I follow that path when I saw that?

858
00:48:46,272 --> 00:48:47,272
I...

859
00:48:47,272 --> 00:48:49,438
I completely understand your concerns.

860
00:48:49,438 --> 00:48:51,405
I will do my utmost to protect Hui Won
and the child from getting hurt.

861
00:48:51,405 --> 00:48:53,338
I'll protect them with everything I have.

862
00:48:53,338 --> 00:48:55,472
So,

863
00:48:55,472 --> 00:48:58,172
please trust me a little

864
00:48:58,172 --> 00:49:00,038
and watch over us.

865
00:49:00,038 --> 00:49:01,738
I'm sorry.

866
00:49:20,438 --> 00:49:22,138
Here.

867
00:49:26,338 --> 00:49:28,338
I'm sorry. This is embarrassing.

868
00:49:28,338 --> 00:49:29,405
What's embarrassing?

869
00:49:29,405 --> 00:49:31,672
It's not your fault.

870
00:49:35,405 --> 00:49:37,672
Actually, I was also

871
00:49:38,305 --> 00:49:41,338
born before my parents got married.

872
00:49:42,938 --> 00:49:44,705
My mom and dad

873
00:49:44,705 --> 00:49:48,938
really liked each other even though
they were young, so that part was fine.

874
00:49:48,938 --> 00:49:54,238
But soon after I was born,
my dad started cheating constantly.

875
00:49:56,005 --> 00:49:58,005
Because of that,

876
00:49:58,005 --> 00:50:02,938
my mom suffered raising me,

877
00:50:02,938 --> 00:50:05,038
and they ended up divorcing

878
00:50:05,038 --> 00:50:08,805
before I even started elementary school.

879
00:50:08,805 --> 00:50:14,272
Now, whenever she sees me,
I guess she thinks of my dad.

880
00:50:15,638 --> 00:50:17,805
Well,

881
00:50:17,805 --> 00:50:19,638
I grew up without receiving love.

882
00:50:19,638 --> 00:50:21,772
That's why

883
00:50:21,772 --> 00:50:24,772
I didn't want to get married either,

884
00:50:25,705 --> 00:50:29,272
and I resent my mom
so much for making me this way,

885
00:50:30,338 --> 00:50:34,305
but I feel like such a fool
because I can't bring myself to leave her.

886
00:50:34,305 --> 00:50:39,738
Anyway, my mom has always been
unfinished homework for me.

887
00:50:41,605 --> 00:50:43,572
I understand completely.

888
00:50:43,572 --> 00:50:46,172
Everyone's got some
unfinished homework in their life.

889
00:50:46,172 --> 00:50:47,905
And mine

890
00:50:51,005 --> 00:50:54,438
is in my hands, my homework.

891
00:51:05,509 --> 00:51:07,685
Uh!

892
00:51:08,572 --> 00:51:10,305
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

893
00:51:26,172 --> 00:51:27,938
Han Jun, pull yourself together!

894
00:51:31,338 --> 00:51:33,105
Hurry, Han Jun!

895
00:51:39,705 --> 00:51:41,238
If this keeps up, you'll be in danger too.

896
00:51:41,238 --> 00:51:42,338
- Don't!
- Let go.

897
00:51:42,338 --> 00:51:44,072
No, I can't.

898
00:51:44,072 --> 00:51:45,938
- Just let go!
- I can't.

899
00:51:45,938 --> 00:51:48,072
Du Jun.

900
00:51:48,072 --> 00:51:49,872
Let go of my hand.

901
00:51:50,738 --> 00:51:52,038
It's my last request.

902
00:51:52,038 --> 00:51:53,672
Don't let go.

903
00:51:53,672 --> 00:51:56,072
Don't give up, please.

904
00:51:56,072 --> 00:51:58,338
Han Jun, no! Han Jun!

905
00:51:58,338 --> 00:52:00,038
Han Jun!

906
00:52:10,372 --> 00:52:14,305
Han Jun! Han Jun!

907
00:52:16,572 --> 00:52:21,072
After that day, whenever someone
touched my hand, even slightly,

908
00:52:21,072 --> 00:52:23,838
my body would freeze automatically.

909
00:52:23,838 --> 00:52:25,938
I'm sorry. I didn't know any of that.

910
00:52:25,938 --> 00:52:27,672
No,

911
00:52:27,672 --> 00:52:29,472
I'm the one who's sorry for
all the misunderstandings.

912
00:52:29,472 --> 00:52:31,338
Everyone has different circumstances,

913
00:52:31,338 --> 00:52:34,438
even if size or weight is different.

914
00:52:34,438 --> 00:52:37,572
So, you don't need to make yourself small.

915
00:52:37,572 --> 00:52:40,738
Don't apologize either, okay?

916
00:52:49,705 --> 00:52:52,172
It must have been terrifying.

917
00:52:53,805 --> 00:52:57,838
Sometimes, no matter how much
you want to prevent it,

918
00:52:57,838 --> 00:53:01,305
there are things beyond your control.

919
00:53:01,972 --> 00:53:04,005
Your brother probably knew it too.

920
00:53:04,005 --> 00:53:08,205
How desperate you were to save him then,

921
00:53:08,205 --> 00:53:13,138
and how much you long for him now.

922
00:53:34,838 --> 00:53:37,038
Thank you for making time.

923
00:53:37,038 --> 00:53:38,805
I can assume that your presence here

924
00:53:38,805 --> 00:53:43,005
means we share the same intentions, right?

925
00:53:44,772 --> 00:53:46,338
Our intentions might align,

926
00:53:46,338 --> 00:53:48,072
but given the high risk,

927
00:53:48,072 --> 00:53:52,472
the executives deserve proper compensation.

928
00:53:54,172 --> 00:53:55,205
Of course.

929
00:53:55,205 --> 00:53:57,872
Early next year, we're launching
the Taehan Hotel chain.

930
00:53:57,872 --> 00:54:03,005
We're planning a total of five branches
in Gangnam, Busan, and Jeju.

931
00:54:04,905 --> 00:54:09,372
If you help us out this time, you'll get
a seven percent stake in each hotel.

932
00:54:09,372 --> 00:54:11,105
Seven percent?

933
00:54:14,472 --> 00:54:18,872
Once I give the signal,
just do your part as planned.

934
00:54:18,872 --> 00:54:22,272
Shall we discuss this in private,
Vice Chairman?

935
00:54:22,272 --> 00:54:24,505
Ah, shall we?

936
00:54:28,005 --> 00:54:30,038
Big news! Big news!

937
00:54:30,038 --> 00:54:31,038
Big news!

938
00:54:31,038 --> 00:54:33,172
- What is it?
- Haven't you all seen the Office Talk chat?

939
00:54:33,172 --> 00:54:34,738
Something interesting?

940
00:54:34,738 --> 00:54:37,072
Ugh, probably just someone complaining
about the company again.

941
00:54:37,072 --> 00:54:38,372
No, that's not it.

942
00:54:38,372 --> 00:54:39,372
At our company,

943
00:54:39,372 --> 00:54:43,838
there's an employee pregnant
with the President's baby!

944
00:54:46,309 --> 00:54:47,672
Is that true?

945
00:54:47,672 --> 00:54:48,672
President's baby?

946
00:54:48,672 --> 00:54:50,038
No, that's just a rumor.

947
00:54:50,038 --> 00:54:51,772
Better make a good impression
on the female employees.

948
00:54:51,772 --> 00:54:53,705
Come on, that can't be true.

949
00:54:56,613 --> 00:54:58,501
It can't be, right?

950
00:55:08,805 --> 00:55:12,869
[Anonymous board]

951
00:55:15,038 --> 00:55:17,272
Whoa, she seduced the President?

952
00:55:17,272 --> 00:55:19,372
With so many eyes on her
at work, she's quite bold!

953
00:55:19,372 --> 00:55:20,505
More like she has two hearts?

954
00:55:20,505 --> 00:55:23,505
Congrats on making your dream of
a successful marriage come true!

955
00:55:23,505 --> 00:55:25,772
Why blame just the employee?
The President could have seduced her.

956
00:55:25,772 --> 00:55:28,638
No way. Gotta admit we've got
literal goddesses at our company though.

957
00:55:28,638 --> 00:55:31,305
Pregnant with the President's kid,
promotion is basically automatic. So jealous.

958
00:55:31,305 --> 00:55:32,305
Why bother with promotion?

959
00:55:32,305 --> 00:55:33,672
She can just quit and live off
his money raising the kid.

960
00:55:33,672 --> 00:55:34,972
The wild part is

961
00:55:34,972 --> 00:55:38,238
that recliner sofa recently
probably is for her?

962
00:55:49,538 --> 00:55:50,805
What? What happened?

963
00:55:50,805 --> 00:55:52,572
- Who was it?
- No idea.

964
00:55:52,572 --> 00:55:56,172
Office Talk is anonymous by nature.

965
00:55:57,205 --> 00:55:58,805
What are you going to do?

966
00:55:58,805 --> 00:56:01,372
I should check on Hui Won.
She must be worried.

967
00:56:01,372 --> 00:56:02,938
Huh? Are you kidding?

968
00:56:02,938 --> 00:56:05,272
Don't you realize all the employees
are watching you right now?

969
00:56:05,272 --> 00:56:06,572
They're all on fire,

970
00:56:06,572 --> 00:56:10,238
trying to see who you talk to
and who you meet.

971
00:56:14,405 --> 00:56:15,905
I'm dying to know who it is.

972
00:56:15,905 --> 00:56:18,538
Seriously, if it were me,
I couldn't come to work.

973
00:56:18,538 --> 00:56:19,538
Is there a way to figure out who she is?

974
00:56:19,538 --> 00:56:21,438
Come on, I think it's just a rumor.

975
00:56:21,438 --> 00:56:25,172
Pregnant women can't drink,
so won't she get caught pretty fast?

976
00:56:25,172 --> 00:56:26,172
Manager Jang.

977
00:56:26,172 --> 00:56:27,672
Do you have anyone in mind as suspicious?

978
00:56:27,672 --> 00:56:30,072
Ah, well...

979
00:56:30,072 --> 00:56:31,838
I'm not sure.

980
00:56:34,672 --> 00:56:38,138
The test batch
of the domestic hop ale beer is ready.

981
00:56:38,138 --> 00:56:40,438
- Test batch?
- It was made based on Manager Jang's idea,

982
00:56:40,438 --> 00:56:42,172
so I want you to try it first.

983
00:56:42,172 --> 00:56:44,672
Here, have a taste.

984
00:56:45,505 --> 00:56:49,738
Oh, Team Leader Bang! What's the occasion?

985
00:56:53,005 --> 00:56:54,905
Manager Jang?

986
00:56:54,905 --> 00:56:58,005
If she's got a boyfriend,
she could just say so.

987
00:57:09,872 --> 00:57:11,772
Can't you see everyone's waiting?

988
00:57:33,738 --> 00:57:34,805
Manager Jang.

989
00:57:34,805 --> 00:57:36,538
Try it.

990
00:57:37,538 --> 00:57:39,772
Are you not drinking or...

991
00:57:39,772 --> 00:57:41,905
Can't you drink?

992
00:57:41,905 --> 00:57:43,505
Well, I...

993
00:57:43,505 --> 00:57:47,138
I think I know why you can't drink.

994
00:57:47,138 --> 00:57:49,038
Manager Jang,

995
00:57:50,272 --> 00:57:52,072
are you pregnant?

996
00:58:02,905 --> 00:58:05,005
What are you doing right now?

997
00:58:17,405 --> 00:58:20,305
[Epilogue]

998
00:58:20,305 --> 00:58:22,705
But you know, when I look at you,
you're really thoughtful.

999
00:58:22,705 --> 00:58:25,405
I have always been a sensitive guy.

1000
00:58:25,405 --> 00:58:27,805
Must have scored points with women that way.

1001
00:58:27,805 --> 00:58:29,072
Points?

1002
00:58:29,072 --> 00:58:33,205
Taking good care of people and treating
them like royalty is my specialty.

1003
00:58:33,205 --> 00:58:34,772
I used to be really popular back in the day.

1004
00:58:34,772 --> 00:58:36,138
Wow, that brings back memories.

1005
00:58:36,138 --> 00:58:38,238
Thanks to you, I really remember now.

1006
00:58:38,238 --> 00:58:39,272
I see.

1007
00:58:39,272 --> 00:58:41,005
Then yesterday must have been quite fun too.

1008
00:58:41,005 --> 00:58:43,738
Yesterday? What was special about yesterday?

1009
00:58:44,872 --> 00:58:47,038
Oh, noona.

1010
00:58:47,805 --> 00:58:49,505
Huh?

1011
00:58:51,705 --> 00:58:53,405
Si Hyeong.

1012
00:58:55,172 --> 00:58:59,638
Stop pretending you
don't know and just spill it.

1013
00:58:59,638 --> 00:59:01,972
I'm all ready to listen.

1014
00:59:03,272 --> 00:59:04,472
Not talking?

1015
00:59:04,472 --> 00:59:06,172
About what?

1016
00:59:06,905 --> 00:59:09,905
Why are you like this? Just say it.

1017
00:59:09,905 --> 00:59:12,372
What is this, some new torture?

1018
00:59:12,372 --> 00:59:15,705
Torture? If anyone heard,
they'd think I'm bullying you.

1019
00:59:15,705 --> 00:59:17,538
- You've been
- Huh?

1020
00:59:17,538 --> 00:59:18,905
- having
- Yeah.

1021
00:59:18,905 --> 00:59:20,105
- quite a good time
- Yeah.

1022
00:59:20,105 --> 00:59:22,572
behind my back lately, haven't you?

1023
00:59:22,572 --> 00:59:24,172
Me?

1024
00:59:24,172 --> 00:59:25,638
Si Hyeong.

1025
00:59:25,638 --> 00:59:28,238
You're really not going to tell me, huh?

1026
00:59:28,238 --> 00:59:30,438
You took my car yesterday,
and I even let you have it.

1027
00:59:30,438 --> 00:59:32,138
Didn't you leave work right away yesterday?

1028
00:59:32,138 --> 00:59:33,772
- I didn't.
- What?

1029
00:59:33,772 --> 00:59:35,238
If you needed a car, you should've called me.

1030
00:59:35,238 --> 00:59:36,772
I was at the office until late.

1031
00:59:36,772 --> 00:59:38,305
I know, you even had late-night snacks.

1032
00:59:38,305 --> 00:59:41,572
Yeah, the late-night snacks were delicious.

1033
00:59:45,672 --> 00:59:47,505
How did you know?

1034
00:59:50,105 --> 00:59:52,105
Who...

1035
00:59:54,272 --> 00:59:56,005
- Never mind.
- Oh, you scared me.

1036
00:59:56,005 --> 00:59:57,005
Keep doing what you were doing.

1037
00:59:57,005 --> 00:59:58,872
I'll handle it myself.

1038
01:00:02,605 --> 01:00:04,305
Jeez.

1039
01:00:09,338 --> 01:00:12,605
I know exactly what he's up to.

1040
01:00:45,005 --> 01:00:46,772
What's the real reason you can't drink?

1041
01:00:46,772 --> 01:00:49,305
Has anyone seen Manager Jang
drinking recently?

1042
01:00:49,305 --> 01:00:50,305
Pregnant?

1043
01:00:50,305 --> 01:00:51,372
Then the person
at the center of that rumor is...

1044
01:00:51,372 --> 01:00:53,438
Taehan Liquor's President Kang Du Jun...

1045
01:00:53,438 --> 01:00:54,605
Du Jun, we're in big trouble.

1046
01:00:54,605 --> 01:00:57,072
There's no woman or child involved.

1047
01:00:57,072 --> 01:01:00,405
Before you get more hurt,
break up with him and run away.

1048
